 Entries for the he 23rd annual Barberton XCM Mountain Bike Challenge hosted by the Barberton Rotary Club has been opened. The race will take place on January 26. The race boasts five different race categories, from the very delicate 20km fun ride to the not so delicate 110km ultra marathon. Read More: This mountain bike challenge is not so delicate at all The pre-entries will close on January 20 at 23h00. Late registration to commence on Friday afternoon, January 25 at 15:00 until 21:00 and Saturday morning from 5:30 to 7:00. All races will start and finish at the Barberton High School. For more information, visits www.barbertonxcm.co.za